<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Dichoptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dichoptera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dichoptera</taxonomicName>
was erected by Spinola in 1939 as one of five dictyopharid genera for the family 
<taxonomicName family="Dictyopharidae" lsidName="" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="family">Dictyopharidae</taxonomicName>
. A total of eleven species are included in the genus, which is restricted in the Oriental region. The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Dichoptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dichoptera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dichoptera</taxonomicName>
was moved by 
<bibRefCitation author="Emeljanov, AF" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Zoologicheskogo Instituta Akademii Nauk SSSR" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="3 - 22" title="The problem of differentiation of the families Fulgoridae and Dictyopharidae." volume="82" year="1979">Emeljanov (1979)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<taxonomicName family="Dictyopharidae" lsidName="" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="family">Dictyopharidae</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName family="Fulgoridae" lsidName="" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="family">Fulgoridae</taxonomicName>
and a taxonomic review on this group is preparing (Song and Liang, in prep.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
